{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:second-timothy.4",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Timothy 4 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:1",
      "text": "I charge thee, before God and Jesus Christ, who shall judge the living and the dead, by his coming and his kingdom:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:2",
      "text": "Preach the word: be instant in season, out of season: reprove, entreat, rebuke in all patience and doctrine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:3",
      "text": "For there shall be a time when they will not endure sound doctrine but, according to their own desires, they will heap to themselves teachers having itching ears:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:4",
      "text": "And will indeed turn away their hearing from the truth, but will be turned unto fables.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:5",
      "text": "But be thou vigilant, labour in all things, do the work of an evangelist, fulfil thy ministry. Be sober.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:6",
      "text": "For I am even now ready to be sacrificed: and the time of my dissolution is at hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:7",
      "text": "I have fought a good fight: I have finished my course: I have kept the faith.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:8",
      "text": "As to the rest, there is laid up for me a crown of justice which the Lord the just judge will render to me in that day: and not only to me, but to them also that love his coming. Make haste to come to me quickly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:9",
      "text": "For Demas hath left me, loving this world, and is gone to Thessalonica:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:10",
      "text": "Crescens into Galatia, Titus into Dalmatia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:11",
      "text": "Only Luke is with me. Take Mark and bring him with thee: for he is profitable to me for the ministry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:12",
      "text": "But Tychicus I have sent to Ephesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:13",
      "text": "The cloak that I left at Troas, with Carpus, when thou comest, bring with thee: and the books, especially the parchments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:14",
      "text": "Alexander the coppersmith hath done me much evil: the Lord will reward him according to his works:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:15",
      "text": "Whom do thou also avoid: for he hath greatly withstood our words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:16",
      "text": "At my first answer, no man stood with me: but all forsook me. May it not be laid to their charge!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:17",
      "text": "But the Lord stood by me and strengthened me, that by me the preaching may be accomplished and that all the Gentiles may hear. And I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:18",
      "text": "The Lord hath delivered me from every evil work and will preserve me unto his heavenly kingdom. To whom be glory for ever and ever. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:19",
      "text": "Salute Prisca, and Aquila and the household of Onesiphorus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:20",
      "text": "Erastus remained at Corinth. And Trophimus I left sick at Miletus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:21",
      "text": "Make haste to come before winter. Eubulus and Pudens and Linus and Claudia and all the brethren, salute thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:second-timothy.4.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "second-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Timothy 4:22",
      "text": "The Lord Jesus Christ be with thy spirit. Grace be with you. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
